hor revisits the Inca cosmology and looks at the way in which the ruler and other authorities connected the people to the gods and bound a diverse polity together under divine protection. Next, the book shows how rituals immortalized these leaders and connected the people to past generations. Finally, the author examines how a cosmology, centered on the divine nature of the king, defined the community and identity of the Andean people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / South America.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362455940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503624559423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503624559/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles